<task id="task_D6C306326CFD404096FCD1F996768ED6"> 
  <title>Disable synchronization of shared folders</title> 
  <shortdesc>How to disable the synchronization of shared Marketing Cloud
	 folders within your Creative Cloud Files folder. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <taskbody> 
	 <context id="context_40B5412B53EF40D5A539586873FF6728"> 
		<note>You can desynchronize only folders that you own.
		</note>
		<p outputclass="head"><b>Windows</b> 
		</p> 
		<ol id="ol_7E442CEEF6494D6B822EBB867E0C17F4"> 
		  <li id="li_E8562DA24AC445FAA52B71E5EA94D0EC"> 
			 <p>Open Windows Explorer. 
			 </p> 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_95565F6F575F4810B1CDEE8787CEC73A"> 
			 <p>Under Favorites, right click the 
				<uicontrol>Creative Cloud Files</uicontrol> folder, then click 
				<uicontrol>Select Shared Folders to Sync</uicontrol>. 
			 </p> 
			 <p><image href="graphics/select_sync_folders.png"
				id="image_089AD6A762404AD49755F2E8D932E530"><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?></image>
				
			 </p> 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_1CC520141C6B4DFAAD00E2D495EE9065"> 
			 <p>Deselect any folder that you do not want to synchronize. 
			 </p> 
		  </li> 
		</ol> 
		<p outputclass="head"><b>Mac OS</b> 
		</p> 
		<ol id="ol_59975983457344FBA1E364DE8EF31D1E"> 
		  <li id="li_EA9E97631E454A54BB42171EF394BDFC"> 
			 <p>Open a Finder window. 
			 </p> 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_2BDCA1CD1E664DE59BFCF81D3A33A2FC"> 
			 <p>Navigate to your user folder. 
			 </p> 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_994D46A141AE497A9291B77AE7918F55"> 
			 <p>Control-click the 
				<uicontrol>Creative Cloud Files</uicontrol>, then click 
				<uicontrol>Select shared folders to sync</uicontrol>. 
			 </p> 
			 <p><image href="graphics/select_sync_folders_mac.png"
				id="image_6CDDD3F6806C43DC95C353A69C1AD5D8"><?xm-replace_text Paragraph?></image>
				
			 </p> 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_1FD89F8D0B6C4867A24789B3EE6E96C0"> 
			 <p> Deselect any folder that you do not want to synchronize. 
			 </p> 
			 <p>Synchronized folders have a checkmark next to the folder name.
			 </p>
		  </li> 
		</ol> 
	 </context> 
  </taskbody> 
</task>
